FBIS3-5199 "dreas043_q_94001" FBIS-EAS-94-043 Document Type:Daily Report 4 Mar 1994 AUSTRALASIA Australia Minister Opposes Sending Troops to Bosnia BK0403063694 Melbourne Radio Australia in English 0500 GMT 4 Mar 94 BK0403063694 Melbourne Radio Australia Language: English Article Type:BFN [Summary From Poor Reception] The United States has ignored an appeal by two United Nations officials in Bosnia for the deployment there of additional troops. Yashushi Akashi, a UN representative in Bosnia, also joined the debate on sending 10,000 more troops to Bosnia. Australian Defense Minister Robert Ray says he opposed sending troops to Bosnia. Ray said the government requires certain conditions to be met before it can consider sending any soldiers.
